# Theme docs — source of truth

## Source files

Theme source code is synced from the upstream GitHub repos into `.src/<theme>/` by running `npm run sync`.
This clones the latest default branch of each theme repo and places the result at `.src/slab/`, `.src/paper/`, `.src/space/`, `.src/keystone/`, etc.

Before writing or editing any theme documentation, read the relevant source files from `.src/<theme>/`.
Do not draft content without first consulting the source. If the required files are not present, ask the user to run `npm run sync` first.

## Verification requirements

- Use `.liquid` files, `{% schema %}` blocks, and locale files in `.src/<theme>/locales/` as the canonical reference.
- Resolve all translated setting labels by looking up their `t:` keys in the locale files before writing setting names.
- Verify defaults, ranges, and option values directly from `{% schema %}` — do not guess or infer them.
- Confirm block compatibility (nesting, supported block types, app-block support) from schema definitions and Liquid usage.
- If behavior differs by template or context, verify the condition from source and state it explicitly in the docs.
- Do not document features, settings, or behaviors that cannot be confirmed in the source files.
